 engaged asset owners.  READ MORE...                  Members   Committed to Prompt, Reliable Pension Information Ontario Teachers' prides itself on offering personalized, immediate service to members at all stages of their lives. Learn more... Get Pension Estimates  Your Ontario Teachers' online account allows you to see how much your pension is worth. It gives you instant access to your personal pension records, any time, anywhere.  Discover more... Stay Informed Get frequent and unique content on pension issues relevant to you. Read more...                                   Corporate         Corporate Overview   About Ontario Teachers'   Plan Governance   Board Members   Executive Team   Annual Reporting   Plan Funding   Careers   Corporate We’re honoured to be recognized as one of the world’s leading pension plans. Learn More    Investments         Overview   Performance   Responsible Investing   Asset Groups   Investment Teams   Partners in Opportunity   Investments Working with partners who share our investment and business goals is the best way to meet our members’ retirement needs Learn More    News   Members   Careers         Careers Overview   The Ontario Teachers' Difference   Working at Ontario Teachers'   Our Culture   What Our Employees Say   Experienced Professionals   Students   Career Opportunities                            Member Sign-In  Change your password Switch accounts Sign out     Home   Contact   Careers    Français   Smaller FontLarger Font         Follow us on:           With $175.6 billion in assets as of December 31, 2016, the Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan is the largest single-profession pension plan in Canada.   An independent organization, it invests the pension fund's assets and administers the pensions of 318,000 active and retired teachers in Ontario.     Home   Contact   Careers   Legal & Privacy   Resources   Site Map    Français                     Contact Us - Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan                                          Contact Us                                        Jean Turmel      Jean Turmel became president of Perseus Capital Inc., a...   Read More About Jean Turmel »                        Member Hotline:  Phone: (416) 226-2700 Toll Free: 1 (800) 668-0105 Fax: (416) 730-7807 Fax Toll Free: 1 (800) 949-8208    Email: Inquiry@otpp.com  Office Hours: 8:00am to 5:30pm Monday to Friday  We never exchange confidential or personal information with you through email. Similarly, you should never send us sensitive information by email.                        Head Office Location:  Office / Visit: Reception: 3rd floor 5650 Yonge Street Toronto, Ontario M2M 4H5  Phone: (416) 228-5900 Toll Free: 1-877-812-7989 Fax: (416) 730-5349  Office Hours: 8:00am to 5:30pm Monday to Friday        Get directions       Head Office Directions and Building Facilities  The Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan is conveniently located in the Xerox Tower, on the northwest corner of Yonge Street and Finch Avenue.  Parking  Parking is available under the building. When parking underground, follow the signs to the Xerox Tower. If you are travelling north from the 401 and Yonge, turn left (west) onto Finch Avenue West and exit to the first driveway on the right. You may also enter the underground parking from Hendon Avenue, which is the first street north of Finch on the west side of Yonge Street. There is also limited parking on Yonge Street.  Wheelchair access  The office building is wheelchair accessible via the underground parking garage or the street-level doors on the east and west sides of the building.  Subway  Take the northbound train on the Yonge line. Get off at Finch station (farthest stop north on the Yonge line). Follow the signs to the Xerox Tower of the North American Life Centre.  Bus  There are a number of buses that service the Finch and Yonge subway terminal each day: There are several TTC bus routes to coming from all ends of the city. GO Transit also provides service from Newmarket and has two buses running from Richmond Hill. Markham Transit has five different buses that reach the Yonge and Finch Terminal.  Car  We're located on the northwest corner of Finch Avenue and Yonge Street. If you are coming from the 401, take the Yonge Street north exit and continue past Sheppard Avenue               Investments  With $175.6 billion in net assets - and a commitment to paying pensions for more than 70 years from now - Ontario Teachers' is continually searching for new investment opportunities.  Hong Kong    Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan (Asia) Limited  28/F Alexandra House 18 Chater Road, Central Hong Kong  Phone: + 852.2230.4500 Fax: + 852.2230.4530 Email: inquiry_asia@otpp.com  Go to the Hong Kong page        Get directions    London    10 Portman Square London, W1H 6AZ  Phone: +44 20 7659 4450 Fax: +44 20 7659 4451 Email: contact_london@otpp.com  Go to the London page        Get directions    New York    375 Park Avenue, Suite 2601 New York, NY 10152  Phone: (212) 888-5799 Fax: (212) 838-2549        Get directions                    Corporate Communications and Media Relations    Deborah Allan, Managing Director  Communications and Media Relations  Phone: (416) 730-5347 Toll Free: 1 (877) 812-7989 x 5347 Fax: (416) 730-6338 E-mail: deborah_allan@otpp.com         Pallavi Armoogum  Corporate Communications  Phone: (416) 730-6450 E-mail: communications@otpp.com    Asia Media Inquiries  Please contact: asiamedia@otpp.com                      Employer Information Services (EIS)   If you are an employer and require information about reporting requirements and plan changes, please contact the Employer Information Services (EIS) department:  Phone: (416) 227-7525 Toll Free: 1 (866) 867-9147 Online: https://employers1.otpp.com              Head Office Directions and Building Facilities  The Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan is conveniently located in the Xerox Tower, on the northwest corner of Yonge Street and Finch Avenue.  Parking  Parking is available under the building. When parking underground, follow the signs to the Xerox Tower. If you are travelling north from the 401 and Yonge, turn left (west) onto Finch Avenue West and exit to the first driveway on the right. You may also enter the underground parking from Hendon Avenue, which is the first street north of Finch on the west side of Yonge Street. There is also limited parking on Yonge Street.  Wheelchair access  The office building is wheelchair accessible via the underground parking garage or the street-level doors on the east and west sides of the building.  Subway  Take the northbound train on the Yonge line. Get off at Finch station (farthest stop north on the Yonge line). Follow the signs to the Xerox Tower of the North American Life Centre.  Bus  There are a number of buses that service the Finch and Yonge subway terminal each day: There are several TTC bus routes to coming from all ends of the city. GO Transit also provides service from Newmarket and has two buses running from Richmond Hill. Markham Transit has five different buses that reach the Yonge and Finch Terminal.  Car  We're located on the northwest corner of Finch Avenue and Yonge Street. If you are coming from the 401, take the Yonge Street north exit and continue past Sheppard Avenue                      Latest Tweets Tweets by @OtppInfo   Follow us on Twitter                       Corporate       Investments       News       Members       Careers                           Member Sign-In  Change your password Switch accounts Sign out     Home   Contact   Careers    Français   Smaller FontLarger Font          Home   Contact   Careers   Legal & Privacy   Resources   Site Map    Français                    







