  The Ontario Teachers' difference  We truly believe that our people drive our success. We provide learning and professional-development opportunities and reward performance, so the best and the brightest not only come here - they stay. Learn more       Working at Ontario Teachers'  Our diverse workforce of highly talented individuals make up our team of world-class professionals, who are recognized globally for their expertise and success.  Learn more         Our culture  Everyone at Ontario Teachers' has a clear role in our vision to be the world's leading pension plan organization, and shares in our culture of innovation, agility and partnership.  Learn more       What our employees say  Our employees tell us they are proud to work at Ontario Teachers' and would recommend Ontario Teachers' to others as a great place to work. Our Employee Survey score continues to increase, indicating that people are highly motivated, proud of and loyal to the organization.  Learn more     Career opportunities  Ontario Teachers' has an outstanding reputation for top performance. We have set the global standard for pension and investment management, and member service. We are looking for people who can help to ensure Ontario Teachers' maintains its position as a world-class pension plan.  Learn more  For students interested in a co-op or summer internship position, please visit our student section for more information about our student recruiting process.  About Ontario Teachers'    Mission, Vision & Values  As a pension plan, we are in the business of understanding the present and how it affects the future. The change that we face has never been faster or deeper. Our Mission, Vision and Values are our roadmap to help guide us in this ever-changing environment and to prepare us for tomorrow. Learn more    History of Innovation  Our employees are leaders in their field. They pioneered many of the investment practices and service standards that are now common in the pension world. Our record of innovation and performance is the result of our objective to help the plan meet its funding needs and support our members – the teachers of Ontario.  Learn more      Awards & Recognition  We are honoured to be recognized as one of the world's leading pension plans. From the best Member Services team to our award-winning Investment teams, here are some of our achievements.  Learn more    Annual Reporting  We provide an annual update on investments, funding and plan operations every April, for the previous year ended December 31. Get highlights of the plan's performance.  Learn more                          Careers Overview The Ontario Teachers' Difference Working at Ontario Teachers' Our Culture What Our Employees Say Experienced Professionals Students Career Opportunities             Follow Us                               Corporate       Investments       News       Members       Careers                           Member Sign-In  Change your password Switch accounts Sign out     Home   Contact   Careers    Français   Smaller FontLarger Font          Home   Contact   Careers   Legal & Privacy   Resources   Site Map    Français                     Featured News - Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan                                          Featured News                                       Ontario Teachers’ is fully funded for fourth consecutive year     March 29, 2017 — Net assets rose to $175.6 billion in 2016; Total-fund rate of return of 4.2%      Topic: Funding, Financial Results, Investments, Corporate Type: Teachers' News Releases                         Recent News          3i announces sale of Mémora generating proceeds of £117 million     July 17, 2017 — 3i Group plc, and funds managed by 3i, announce sale of Mémora, the leading Iberian funeral...      Topic: Investments Type: Teachers' News Releases      Strategic review concludes with sale of High Speed 1     July 14, 2017 — Borealis and Ontario Teachers' have entered into a definitive agreement to 