 engaged asset owners.  READ MORE...                  Members   Committed to Prompt, Reliable Pension Information Ontario Teachers' prides itself on offering personalized, immediate service to members at all stages of their lives. Learn more... Get Pension Estimates  Your Ontario Teachers' online account allows you to see how much your pension is worth. It gives you instant access to your personal pension records, any time, anywhere.  Discover more... Stay Informed Get frequent and unique content on pension issues relevant to you. Read more...                                   Corporate         Corporate Overview   About Ontario Teachers'   Plan Governance   Board Members   Executive Team   Annual Reporting   Plan Funding   Careers   Corporate We’re honoured to be recognized as one of the world’s leading pension plans. Learn More    Investments         Overview   Performance   Responsible Investing   Asset Groups   Investment Teams   Partners in Opportunity   Investments Working with partners who share our investment and business goals is the best way to meet our members’ retirement needs Learn More    News   Members   Careers         Careers Overview   The Ontario Teachers' Difference   Working at Ontario Teachers'   Our Culture   What Our Employees Say   Experienced Professionals   Students   Career Opportunities                            Member Sign-In  Change your password Switch accounts Sign out     Home   Contact   Careers    Français   Smaller FontLarger Font         Follow us on:           With $175.6 billion in assets as of December 31, 2016, the Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan is the largest single-profession pension plan in Canada.   An independent organization, it invests the pension fund's assets and administers the pensions of 318,000 active and retired teachers in Ontario.     Home   Contact   Careers   Legal & Privacy   Resources   Site Map    Français                   


Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan - Wikipedia





















 






Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This article relies too much on references to primary sources. Please improve this by adding secondary or tertiary sources. (July 2017) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)



Ontario Teachers' Pension Plan Board





Type

Private


Industry
Pension fund


Founded
1989; 28 years ago (1989)


